cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.LG 

This paper deals with perceptual quality assessment of synthesized textures, which involves analyzing the spatial and statistical attributes of texture images. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The use of wavelet coefficients suggests a potential connection to signal processing (cs.IT), while the focus on visual quality assessment could also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and machine learning (cs.LG) subfields.
